METAGOOFIL
A tool used to extract metadata (usernames, emails, software info) from public documents on a website.

Real‑time Example using Metagoofil
Suppose you want to extract metadata from documents on IBM website.

1️⃣ Run Metagoofil
metagoofil -d ibm.com -t pdf,doc,xls,ppt -l 20 -n 10 -o results -f ibm_report.html
2️⃣ What this Command Does

-d ibm.com → Target domain

-t pdf,doc,xls,ppt → Search document types

-l 20 → Limit search results

-n 10 → Download 10 files

-o results → Save downloaded files

-f ibm_report.html → Create HTML report

3️⃣ Example Information Found

From document metadata you may discover:

👤 Usernames (example: john.smith)

📧 Emails (example: john.smith@ibm.com)

💻 Software used (example: Microsoft Office)

🖥 Internal computer names

✅ Example output

Usernames found:
john.smith
admin.ibmdoc

Emails found:
john.smith@ibm.com
security@ibm.com

💡 Why hackers / pentesters use this tool

Find employee usernames

Discover internal system names

Help in social engineering attacks

Metadata is data that describes other data. 📄🔍

Simple Example

A document file may contain hidden information such as:

👤 Author name

📅 Date created

💻 Software used

🖥 Computer name
