WAYBACK MACHINE:
A tool that shows old versions of websites saved from previous years.
It works like a time machine for websites.

You enter a website URL

It shows how the website looked in the past

Example

If you search google.com, you can see:

Google website in 2005

Google website in 2010

Google website in 2020

SYNTAX:
1️⃣ Get all archived URLs
echo "ibm.com" | waybackurls
2️⃣ Find Old Login Pages
echo "ibm.com" | waybackurls | grep login
3️⃣ Find Old Directory Structure
echo "ibm.com" | waybackurls | grep "/"
4️⃣ Save Results
echo "ibm.com" | waybackurls > ibm_old_urls.txt

✅ This helps you discover:

🔑 Old login pages

📂 Old directories

🗂 Hidden or deleted pages from the past.
